1.00	Hesper,_Kansas	Hesper, Kansas	Hesper is an unincorporated community in Douglas County, Kansas located two and a half miles southeast of Eudora. Hesper was founded in 1858 by Quakers wanting to lend support to the free-state cause. In 1884, the Hesper Academy was opened but it closed in 1912.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Hesper_Friends_Church.jpg/250px-Hesper_Friends_Church.jpg
